definitions.definition: Of consonants : having the same place of articulation . For example, labial m, b, p , alveolar n, d, t , velar ŋ, g, k . Indic alphabets such as Devanagari , as well as the Korean hangul alphabet, are rationally arranged so that homorganic consonants are grouped together.
produced by the same or homologous organs

main_definition: ( phonetics ) Of consonants : having the same place of articulation . For example, labial m, b, p , alveolar n, d, t , velar ŋ, g, k . Indic alphabets such as Devanagari , as well as the Korean hangul alphabet, are rationally arranged so that homorganic consonants are grouped together.
secondary_definitions: ( medicine ) produced by the same or homologous organs
